cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN)-based model for joint object categorization and pose estimation using multi-view images. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks such as object classification and pose estimation, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also uses unsupervised learning techniques to learn latent variables, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper's focus on pose estimation and alignment strategies is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques is relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
